host.description: The hostname of the proxy server.

port.description: The port of the proxy server.

protocol.description: The protocol of the proxy server.  Use "http" or "https".  Defaults to "http" if not specified.

principal.description: The principal (aka username) of the credentials for the proxy server.

password.description: The password for the credentials for the proxy server.

ntlmDomain.description: The ntlm domain for the proxy server.

principal.description: The principal (aka username) of the credentials for the proxy server.

password.description: The password for the credentials for the proxy server.

ntlmDomain.description: The ntlm domain for the proxy server.

PatchDocument.description: A JSONPatch document as defined by RFC 6902

value.description: The value to be used within the operations.

from.description: A string containing a JSON Pointer value.

BulkBody.description: Body composed of stringified JSON lines, each one representing an entity

BulkPatchBody.description: Body composed of stringified JSON-Patch lines, each one representing updates to an entity

Unknown.description: value used by the openapi generator when no matching type found. Should be fixed in a near future.

Null.description: no value object, used to represent a None option value

Empty.description: an empty body. Useful for RPC like endpoints

error_description.description: A short description of the error if one

Otoroshi-Error.description: sometimes, the error name is here

Otoroshi-Error-Msg.description: sometimes, the error description is here

error.description: the error of the operation if one

default_config.description: the default config of the plugin (for UI form)

plugin_visibility.description: visibility of the plugin (can be internal or userland)

ServiceFromOpenApiBody.description: Properties to create a service from an openapi spec
